UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2355
1 AN ACT relating to outdoor recreation.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 147A.090 is amended to read as follows:
4 Each district board of directors shall have the power, duty, and authority to:
5 (1) Establish such functional advisory committees as may be necessary and advisable.
6 These functional advisory committees shall be organized to meet such guidelines as
7 may be required for federal or state assistance;
8 (2) Conduct the necessary research and studies and coordinate and cooperate with all
9 appropriate groups and agencies in order to develop, and adopt and revise, when
10 necessary, a district development plan or series of plans, including, but not limited
11 to, the following districtwide plan elements:
12 (a) Goals and objectives;
13 (b) Water and sewer;
14 (c) Land-use; and
15 (d) Open space and recreation.
16 Such plans shall serve as a general guide for public and private actions and
17 decisions to assure the development of public and private property in the most
18 appropriate relationships;
19 (3) Prepare annually a report of its activities to the cities and counties within the
20 district, the legislature, and the Governor. The board shall make copies of the report
21 available to members of the public within the district;
22 (4) Comply with the provisions of KRS 65A.010 to 65A.090;
23 (5) Cooperate with the Kentucky Mountain Regional Recreation Authority established
24 in KRS 148.0222 for the purpose of establishing, maintaining, and promoting
25 recreational trails to increase economic development, tourism, and outdoor
26 recreation for Kentucky's residents and visitors, not only in eastern Kentucky but
27 throughout the Commonwealth; and
